# Contributing to Tiny Walnut Games Projects

Thank you for your interest in contributing! Contributions are welcome and appreciated. Please follow these guidelines to help maintain a high-quality codebase and collaborative environment.

## How to Contribute

1. **Fork the Repository**  
   Create your own fork and work from a feature branch.

2. **Open an Issue**  
   Before submitting a pull request, open an issue to discuss your proposed changes or bugfixes.

3. **Coding Standards**  
   - Use C# 9.0 features where appropriate.
   - Follow Unity and .NET Framework 4.7.1 best practices.
   - Keep code readable, well-documented, and consistent with the existing style.

4. **Pull Requests**  
   - Reference the related issue in your PR description.
   - Keep PRs focused and minimal; avoid unrelated changes.
   - Ensure your code builds and passes all tests.

5. **Localization and Assets**  
   - For localization, use the provided XLIFF workflow.
   - Only include assets you have the right to distribute.

6. **Review Process**  
   - All PRs will be reviewed for code quality, clarity, and alignment with project goals.
   - Be responsive to feedback and willing to make changes.

## Reporting Issues

- Use the issue tracker for bugs, feature requests, and questions.
- Provide clear steps to reproduce bugs and include relevant logs or screenshots.

## Community Standards

- Be respectful and constructive in all communications.
- See the [Code of Conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) for more details.

Thank you for helping make this project better!
